Script strings (IR):
    0: "Oh, I'd forgotten!\r\nThanks for the great \r\nbirthday present!\x05"
    1: "What a fantastic gift!\r\nHow did you know I love\r\nthese so much? Thanks!\x05"
    2: "This is for me? \r\nGee, thanks...I love these!\x05"
    3: "Wow, thanks...\r\nI'll remember this!\x05"
    4: "Err...Thanks...\x05"
    5: "Are you trying to goad\r\nme into losing my temper, \r\n\xFF!?\x05"
    6: "I guess you're used to \r\nbugs, if you work on \r\na farm!\x05"
    7: "Yikes!\r\nGet it away from me!\x05"
    8: "Now this is a great one...!\r\nThanks! I think I'll give \r\nit to Harris' wife when\x05\r\nhe gets married!\x05"
    9: "Well this is very fancy!\x05\x0COh...You mean it's for me?\r\nI can't exactly use it,\r\nbut I'll give it to \x05\r\nHarris' wife when he gets\x05\r\nmarried.\x05"
    10: "I bet the animals get\r\nscared when you put this on!\x05\x0COh, it's for me? Thanks!\x05"
    11: "Congratulations!\r\nWho's the lucky girl, \r\nif I may ask?\x05"
    12: "Have you heard of the\r\nForget-me-not Valley?\x05\x0CI hear there's someone \r\nthere named \xFF,\r\nwho is very popular. \x05\x0CI'd like to meet him...\x05"
    13: "A long time ago, someone\r\nnamed Kano used to stay at\r\nmy house. \x05\x0CHe used to love taking \r\npictures of Mineral Town.\x05\x0COne day, though, he just \r\nleft a letter and vanished.\x05\x0CI wonder where he is now?\x05"
    14: "There's nothing more \r\npleasing to a mayor than \r\na peaceful village!\x05"
    15: "You should at least \r\nrest on the weekends, \r\n\xFF!!\x05"
    16: "I bet that's not going\r\nto happen though, is it?\x05"
    17: "Hmmm...Looks like it's not\r\ngoing to stop. \x05\x0CAnd I was going to go to \r\nthe Square, too!\x05"
    18: "Ellen and I always eat \r\nApple Pie together on the\r\nweekends. \x05\x0CThe Apple Pie at the \r\nInn is the best!\x05"
    19: "Hi, \xFF!. \r\nI'm off to go shopping!\x05"
    20: "Well, if it isn't \r\n\xFF!. \x05\x0CHow are you enjoying \r\nlife on the farm?\x05"
    21: "I'm sure it will take some\r\ngetting used to.\x05\x0CA farm is a complicated \r\nplace, after all!\x05"
    22: "Hi, \xFF!!\r\nHave you gotten the hang\r\nof farming, yet?\x05"
    23: "Myself...I know more about\r\nrunning towns than farms!\x05"
    24: "Hi, \xFF!!\r\nI hear you've been doing\r\nmighty well at the farm!\x05"
    25: "People like me depend on\r\npeople like you to grow our\r\nfood, \x05\r\nso you have my gratitude!\x05"
    26: "Hey there, \xFF!. \r\nDid you come here for a \r\nrest, too?\x05"
    27: "I bet the animals are happy\r\non days like today, eh?\x05"
    28: "Hello, \xFF!. \r\nHave you come to like \r\nour town yet?\x05"
    29: "Just come to me if you\r\never get into any trouble.\r\nI give great advice.\x05"
    30: "Do you think this \r\nrain will continue...?\x05"
    31: "I was going to the Square, \r\nso I wish it were sunny...\x05\x0CIs there something new up \r\non the bulletin board?\r\nI forget.\x05"
    32: "Too bad about this rain...\x05\x0CAnd it's my day off, too!\x05"
    33: "Harris always comes by the \r\nInn at this hour, so I like\r\nto wait for him here on \x05\r\nrainy days.\x05\x0CJust to make sure everything\r\nis OK, you understand.\x05"
*/
